<!-- WHAT WE TEST -->
<section class="what">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Our Standard</span>
      <h2>What we test, and why.</h2>
      <p>Testing the raw ingredient isn't enough. We test the finished capsule — because that's what you actually swallow.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wgrid reveal">
      <div class="wcard">
        <span class="n">01 / IDENTITY</span>
        <h3>Is it really NMN?</h3>
        <p>High-performance liquid chromatography confirms the compound is what the label says, at the purity claimed. Adulteration in this category is well documented.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="wcard">
        <span class="n">02 / POTENCY</span>
        <h3>Is the dose real?</h3>
        <p>We verify the finished capsule contains the milligrams printed on the label — within tolerance — rather than trusting the supplier's paperwork.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="wcard">
        <span class="n">03 / SAFETY</span>
        <h3>Is anything else in there?</h3>
        <p>Heavy metals, microbial contamination, and residual solvents are screened against pharmacopoeial limits. A batch that fails does not ship.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HONESTY -->
<section class="honest">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="hbox reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Being Straight With You</span>
      <h3>What a Certificate of Analysis does and doesn't prove.</h3>
      <p><strong>It proves composition, not efficacy.</strong> A CoA tells you the capsule contains what we claim, at the purity we claim, free of contaminants we screen for. It says nothing about whether NMN will make you feel different.</p>
      <p><strong>It's a snapshot of one batch.</strong> Each report covers the batch it names. That's precisely why we publish every batch rather than a single flattering one.</p>
      <p><strong>Testing standards vary between labs.</strong> We name our lab and link their accreditation so you can judge the source, not just the number.</p>
      <p><strong>We don't test for everything.</strong> No one does. We publish the panel we run so you know exactly what was and wasn't checked.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="close">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2 class="reveal">Trust should be <em>verifiable,</em> not assumed.</h2>
    <p class="reveal">NMN–01 · 120 capsules · a 60-day supply.</p>
    <div class="reveal"><a href="/pages/shop" class="btn">Shop NMN–01</a></div>
  </div>
</section>

